article.headline: Liberty 118, VMI 108
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Alex McLean scored 40 points and had 19 rebounds and Larry Blair had 28 points to lead Liberty to a 118-108 win over VMI on Wednesday night. McLean shot 16-for-22 in a game that shattered records for both teams. A dunk by McLean with 17:25 left in the first put Liberty (13-16, 7-6 Big South) in the lead for good. A 3-pointer by Reggie Williams with 2:36 to go pulled VMI within 6, but the Keydets could get no closer the rest of the way. Dwight Brewington had 26 points and 8 rebounds and Anthony Smith added 14 points for the Flames. Williams led VMI (12-17, 5-8) with 34 points, and Chavis Holmes added 26. Liberty outshot VMI 64.4 percent from the field to 41.7 percent and outrebounded the Keydets 61-22. Williams set a VMI all-time record for points in a season with 831 and Blair set a Big South career scoring record with 2,177 points.
